renches], ''The New York Times'', October 20, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> Seahawks defensive end [[Jacob Green]] outplayed [[offensive tackle]] [[Karl Nelson]] and recorded a career-high four sacks.<ref name=\"Seahawks\"/> Phil Simms threw four interceptions but coach Bill Parcells denied he was struggling, \"[y]ou'd like not to take a sack in the scoring zone, but sometimes it's hard to know when to throw it away. Two of Phil's interceptions were rebounds that had nothing to do with the quarterback. On the interception on fourth and 14 at the end, he was trying to make a play. I think I would have thrown there, too. The other interception was his mistake. I don't think he's in a slump.\"<ref name=\"int\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50717F63D5B0C728EDDA90994DE484D81 Giants are seeking to Mend Offense], ''The New York Times'', October 21, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryStyle|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 7: New York Giants at Seattle Seahawks\n |date=October 19, 1986\n |time=4:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]\n |road=Giants (5\u20132)\n |R1=0|R2=9|R3=0|R4=3|RT=12\n |home='''Seahawks (5\u20132)'''\n |H1=7|H2=0|H3=3|H4=7|HT=17\n |stadium=[[Kingdome]]\n |attendance=62,282\n |weather=indoors (dome)\n |referee=[[Gene Barth]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Pat Summerall]] (play-by-play), [[John Madden (American football)|John Madden]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198610190sea.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Giants|HomeName=Seahawks|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=7:51\n| Team=Seahawks\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Gordon Hudson|Hudson]]\n| QB=[[Dave Krieg|Krieg]]\n| yards=16\n| ki