th 98 seconds remaining.<ref name=\"Redskins\"/> The Giants offense featured a two tight end formation throughout much of the game which allowed them to run the ball more effectively.<ref name=\"twotight\">Janofsky, Michael. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F5071FF73C590C7B8EDDA90994DE484D81 2 Tight-End Setup Helps Giants Win], ''The New York Times'', October 28, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> The Giants used [[Mark Bavaro]] and Zeke Mowatt throughout much of the game, sometimes even lining them up on the same side.<ref name=\"twotight\"/> Morris finished the game with 181&nbsp;yards.<ref name=\"Lead\"/> Redskins quarterback [[Jay Schroeder]] threw for 420&nbsp;yards in the loss.<ref>Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F5071EF639540C7A8CDDAB0994DE484D81 Giants Were Winners in Battle of Wits], ''The New York Times'', December 9, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 8: Washington Redskins at New York Giants\n |date=October 27, 1986\n |time=9:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n |road=Redskins (6\u20132)\n |R1=0|R2=3|R3=14|R4=3|RT=20\n |home='''Giants (6\u20132)'''\n |H1=3|H2=10|H3=7|H4=7|HT=27\n |stadium=[[Giants Stadium]]\n |attendance=75,923\n |weather={{convert|52|F}}, relative humidity 97%, wind {{convert|14|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Jerry Seeman]]\n |TV=[[Monday Night Football|ABC]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Al Michaels]] (play-by-play), [[Frank Gifford]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198610270nyg.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Redskins|HomeName=Giants|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=10:00\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=37\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=12:28\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=11\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=10\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=3:21\n| Team=Redskins\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=23\n| Kicker=[[Max Zendejas|Zendejas]]\n| Visitor=3\n| Home=10\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=0:00\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=44\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=3\n| Home=13\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=9:04\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Bobby Johnson (American football)|Johnson]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=25\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=3\n| Home=20\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=6:57\n| Team=Redskins\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[George Rogers (American football)|Rogers]]\n| yards=1\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Max Zendejas|Zendejas]]\n| Visitor=10\n| Home=20\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=4:12\n| Team=Redskins\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Gary Clark|Clark]]\n| QB=[[Jay Schroeder|Schroeder]]\n| yards=42\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Max Zendejas|Zendejas]]\n| Visitor=17\n| Home=20\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=4:06\n| Team=Redskins\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=29\n| Kicker=[[Max Zendejas|Zendejas]]\n| Visitor=20\n| Home=20\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=1:38\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=13\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=20\n| Home=27\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=20|Home=27}}\n\n====Week 9: vs. Dallas Cowboys====\n{{See also|1986 Dallas Cowboys season}}\n\nThe Giants played the Cowboys at Giants Stadium in week nine.<ref name=\"Boys\">Litsky, Frank. The Beat Gets Stronger for Jets (8\u20131) and Giants (7\u20132), ''The New York Times'', November 3, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> Defensive end [[George Martin (American football)|George Martin]] recorded a late sack, termed by head coach Bill Parcells as the biggest play of the game, to help the Giants to a 17\u201314 victory.<ref name=\"Boys\"/> The Giants held running backs Tony Dorsett to 45&nbsp;yards in 10 carries and Herschel Walker to 34&nbsp;yards in 10 carries.<ref name=\"Boys\"/> The Cowboys outgained the Giants 408 to 245 in total yardage, and had 25 first downs compared with the Giants' 14.<ref>[http://databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=2&mth=11&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL Box Score Cowboys Vs Giants 11/2/1986] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060526062957/http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=2&mth=11&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL |date=May 26, 2006 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> Phil Simms struggled and completed only 6 of 18 passes for 67&nbsp;yards,<ref name=\"Vikings\"/> but Joe Morris rushed 29 times for 181&nbsp;yards and two touchdowns as the Giants improved to 7\u20132.<ref name=\"Boys\"/>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 9: Dallas Cowboys at New York Giants\n |date=November 2, 1986\n |time=1:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n |road=Cowboys (6\u20133)\n |R1=0|R2=7|R3=0|R4=7|RT=14\n |home='''Giants (7\u20132)'''\n |H1=3|H2=7|H3=0|H4=7|HT=17\n |stadium=[[Giants Stadium]]\n |attendance=74,871\n |weather={{convert|59|F}}, relative humidity 83%, wind {{convert|14|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Dick Hantak]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Pat Summerall]] (play-by-play), [[John Madden (American football)|John Madden]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198611020nyg.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Cowboys|HomeName=Giants|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=2:29\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=25\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=11:00\n| Team=Cowboys\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Mike Renfro|Renfro]]\n| QB=[[Steve Pelluer|Pelluer]]\n| yards=11\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Rafael Septien|Septien]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=6:24\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=8\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=10\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=12:24\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=6\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=7:29\n| Team=Cowboys\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Tony Dorsett|Dorsett]]\n| yards=23\n| kickresult=ggood\n| Kicker=[[Rafael Septien|Septien]]\n| Visitor=14\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=14|Home=17}}\n\n====Week 10: at Philadelphia Eagles====\n{{See also|1986 Philadelphia Eagles season}}\n\nIn week 10, the Giants then travelled to Philadelphia to play the Eagles.<ref name=\"Ground\">Litsky, Frank [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50713FC3E550C728DDDA80994DE484D81 Jets Stay in Air; Giants Grounded; Robinson Gets Better], November 11, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> In a physical game marked by several scuffles,<ref name=\"Clamp\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50712F73D5A0C738DDDA80994DE484D81 Giants Put a Clamp on Eagles], ''The New York Times'', November 10, 1986, accessed May 18, 2007.</ref> the Giants passing game struggled as several receivers played with injuries, and quarterback Phil Simms completed only one pass to a wide receiver; a 17-yarder to [[Solomon Miller]].<ref name=\"Ground\"/> Coach Bill Parcells placed the blame for the passing game's performance on dropped passes by the receivers. \"You can't throw the ball much better than Phil did yesterday\", commented Parcells. \"But he didn't have the numbers to show for it.\"<ref name=\"Ground\"/> The Eagles rushed for 153&nbsp;yards and outgained the Giants 265 to 237 in total yards.<ref>[http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=9&mth=11&yr=1986&tm=PHI&lg=NFL Box Score Giants Vs Eagles 11/9/1986] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060920130714/http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=9&mth=11&yr=1986&tm=PHI&lg=NFL |date=September 20, 2006 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 20, 2007.</ref> The Giants won 17\u201314 nonetheless despite Simms completing only 14 of 36 passes overall. The Giants rode their running attack as Joe Morris passed the 100&nbsp;yard mark for the fourth consecutive game; Morris totalled 116, 181, 181 and 111&nbsp;yards in that period.<ref name=\"Ground\"/> Lawrence Taylor recorded three sacks of the Giants defense seven sacks in the victory.<ref name=\"Clamp\"/>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 10: New York Giants at Philadelphia Eagles\n |date=November 9, 1986\n |time=4:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n |road='''Giants (8\u20132)'''\n |R1=0|R2=10|R3=7|R4=0|RT=17\n |home=Eagles (3\u20137)\n |H1=0|H2=0|H3=0|H4=14|HT=14\n |stadium=[[Veterans Stadium]]\n |attendance=60,601\n |weather={{convert|64|F}}, realative humidity 93%, wind {{convert|12|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Fred Wyant]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Pat Summerall]] (play-by-play), [[John Madden (American football)|John Madden]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198611090phi.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Giants|HomeName=Eagles|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=10:20\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=18\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=0:01\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=25\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=10\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=10:04\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=3\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=17\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=8:49\n| Team=Eagles\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Mike Quick|Quick]]\n| QB=[[Randall Cunningham|Cunningham]]\n| yards=75\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Paul McFadden|McFadden]]\n| Visitor=17\n| Home=7\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=0:45\n| Team=Eagles\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Randall Cunningham|Cunningham]]\n| yards=4\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Paul McFadden|McFadden]]\n| Visitor=17\n| Home=14\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=17|Home=14}}\n\n====Week 11: at Minnesota Vikings====\n{{See also|1986 Minnesota Vikings season}}\n\nTrailing the [[Minnesota Vikings]] 20\u201319 with 72 seconds left in the fourth quarter at the [[Hubert H. Humphrey Metrodome|Metrodome]] in week 11, Phil Simms completed a desperate 22-yard pass on fourth and 17 to Bobby Johnson for a first down.<ref name=\"Po29\">Pooley. pg. 29</ref><ref name=\"Litsky\"/> The completion led to [[Raul Allegre]]'s fifth field goal and an important Giants victory 22\u201320.<ref name=\"Vikings\"/> In the Giants' three previous games, Simms had completed only six passes to wide receivers. In the Giants' victory he completed eight to wide receivers, four to tight end Mark Bavaro and 13 to his running backs\u2014four to [[Ottis Anderson]] in the final two drives, three to [[Maurice Carthon]], three to Joe Morris and three to [[Tony Galbreath]].<ref name=\"Vikings\">[[Dave Anderson (sportswriter)|Anderson, Dave]]. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50716F6345E0C748DDDA80994DE484D81 Sports Of The Times; Phil Simms's Biggest Pass], ''The New York Times'', November 17, 1986. accessed March 20, 2007.</ref> Simms commented years later, \"[i]t's my favorite game in my career, because it's everything I always wanted to be as a player. I wanted to be tough, making big throws, immune to pressure, not worried about outcomes. It was truly like standing on the tee box in golf and there's trees on each side and water and you just go 'Man, I'm gonna rip it down the middle.' And no other thought crosses your mind.\"<ref>Schwartz. pg. 161</ref> The game has frequently been credited as a signature game of their season, and the Giants players celebrated the victory in the tunnel leading to their locker room and in the locker room itself in a raucous manner that was highly atypical for the team. \"They high-fived themselves silly\", recalled [[Peter King (sportswriter)|Peter King]]. \"They were screaming and hooting and raising hell\u2014happier than they had been all year.\"<ref name=\"Po29\"/>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 11: New York Giants at Minnesota Vikings\n |date=November 16, 1986\n |time=1:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n |road='''Giants (9\u20132)'''\n |R1=3|R2=6|R3=3|R4=10|RT=22\n |home=Vikings (6\u20135)\n |H1=3|H2=3|H3=7|H4=7|HT=20\n |stadium=[[Hubert H. Humphrey Metrodome]]\n |attendance=62,003\n |weather=indoors (dome)\n |referee=[[Pat Haggerty (American football official)|Pat Haggerty]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Tim Ryan (sportscaster)|Tim Ryan]] (play-by-play), [[Terry Bradshaw]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198611160min.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Giants|HomeName=Vikings|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=7:48\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=41\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=3\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=1:19\n| Team=Vikings\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=39\n| Kicker=[[Chuck Nelson|Nelson]]\n| Visitor=3\n| Home=3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=12:46\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=37\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=6\n| Home=3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=6:53\n| Team=Vikings\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=44\n| Kicker=[[Chuck Nelson|Nelson]]\n| Visitor=6\n| Home=6\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=2:23\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=24\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=9\n| Home=6\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=8:34\n| Team=Vikings\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Allen Rice|Rice]]\n| QB=[[Tommy Kramer|Kramer]]\n| yards=8\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Chuck Nelson|Nelson]]\n| Visitor=9\n| Home=13\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=1:08\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=37\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=12\n| Home=13\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=9:30\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Bobby Johnson (American football)|Johnson]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=25\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=19\n| Home=13\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=6:53\n| Team=Vikings\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Anthony Carter (American football)|Carter]]\n| QB=[[Wade Wilson (American football)|Wilson]]\n| yards=33\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Chuck Nelson|Nelson]]\n| Visitor=19\n| Home=20\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=0:12\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=33\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=22\n| Home=20\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=22|Home=20}}\n\n====Week 12: vs. Denver Broncos====\n{{See also|1986 Denver Broncos season}}\n\nIn week 12, in what would turn out to be a preview of Super Bowl XXI, veteran [[defensive end]] [[George Martin (American football)|George Martin]] (at 34 the oldest player on the team<ref name=\"Litsky\"/>) intercepted a pass from [[Denver Broncos]] quarterback [[John Elway]] and returned it 78&nbsp;yards for a touchdown before being tackled from behind in the end zone by a celebrating Lawrence Taylor.<ref name=\"Litsky\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F5071FFF3B5F0C778EDDA80994DE484D81 Giants At 10\u20132; Redskins Stay Even; Allegre Kick At :006 Tops Broncos], ''The New York Times'', November 24, 1986. accessed March 20, 2007.</ref> Then in the final two minutes of the game, Simms hit fan\u2013favorite [[Phil McConkey]] for a 46-yard pass.<ref name=\"Litsky\"/> This led to another game-winning kick from Allegre as the Giants defeated Denver 19\u201316 in front of 75,116 fans at Giants Stadium.<ref name=\"Litsky\"/> With the victory the Giants completed their second five-game winning streak of the season, several of them in close contests; the margin of victory in those five games was 7, 3, 3, 2, and 3 points.<ref name=\"Litsky\"/>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapsed\n |title=Week 12: Denver Broncos at New York Giants\n |date=November 23, 1986\n |time=1:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n |road=Broncos (9\u20133)\n |R1=3|R2=3|R3=3|R4=7|RT=16\n |home='''Giants (10\u20132)'''\n |H1=0|H2=10|H3=3|H4=6|HT=19\n |stadium=[[Giants Stadium]]\n |attendance=75,116\n |weather={{convert|43|F}}, relative humidity 70%, wind {{convert|10|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Tom Dooley (American football official)|Tom Dooley]]\n |TV=[[NFL on NBC|NBC]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Dick Enberg]] (play-by-play), [[Merlin Olsen]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-refernece.com/boxscores/198611230nyg.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Broncos|HomeName=Giants|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=6:46\n| Team=Broncos\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=40\n| Kicker=[[Rich Karlis|Karlis]]\n| Visitor=3\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=14:57\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=31\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=3\n| Home=3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=2:38\n| Team=Broncos\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=32\n| Kicker=[[Rich Karlis|Karlis]]\n| Visitor=6\n| Home=3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=0:43\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=IntTD\n| Def=[[George Martin (American football)|Martin]]\n| yards=75\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=6\n| Home=10\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=9:46\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=45\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=6\n| Home=13\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=1:53\n| Team=Broncos\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=42\n| Kicker=[[Rich Karlis|Karlis]]\n| Visitor=9\n| Home=13\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=10:07\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=46\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=9\n| Home=16\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=1:55\n| Team=Broncos\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Sammy Winder|Winder]]\n| yards=4\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Rich Karlis|Karlis]]\n| Visitor=16\n| Home=16\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=0:06\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=34\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=16\n| Home=19\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=16|Home=19}}\n\n====Week 13: at San Francisco 49ers====\n{{See also|1986 San Francisco 49ers season}}\n\nIn a Monday night encounter at San Francisco in week 13, the Giants overcame a 17\u20130 halftime deficit to [[Joe Montana]]'s 49ers en route to a 21\u201317 victory.<ref name=\"49ers\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50712FE3E5C0C718CDDAB0994DE484D81 One Quarter buys playoff ticket for Giants], ''The New York Times'', December 2, 1986. accessed March 26, 2007.</ref> In the win, Simms threw for nearly 400&nbsp;yards and wide receiver [[Stacy Robinson]] made an acrobatic catch at the goalline to set up the winning touchdown.<ref name=\"49ers\"/> Another important play also occurred during that ''Monday Night Football'' game. Here is a description of the play taken from a ''Monday Night Football'' broadcast in 2005: \"On Dec. 1 1986, New York Giants tight end Mark Bavaro cements his reputation as one of the toughest men in the NFL. With the Giants trailing, Bavaro catches an innocent pass from Phil Simms over the middle. It takes nearly seven 49ers defenders to finally drag him down, some of which are carried for almost 20&nbsp;yards, including future Hall of Famer [[Ronnie Lott]]. Bavaro's inspiring play jump starts the Giants, who win the game and eventually the Super Bowl.\"<ref>[http://media.espn.com/MediaZone/PressKits/NFL2005/MNF_list.htm MNF 36: The List Monday Night Football Special (Original Air Date: Aug. 25, 2005)], ESPN.com. accessed January 3, 2007.</ref>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 13: New York Giants at San Francisco 49ers\n |date=December 1, 1986\n |time=9:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n |road='''Giants (11\u20132)'''\n |R1=0|R2=0|R3=21|R4=0|RT=21\n |home=49ers (7\u20135\u20131)\n |H1=3|H2=14|H3=0|H4=0|HT=17\n |stadium=[[Candlestick Park]]\n |attendance=59,777\n |weather={{convert|51|F}}, relative humidity 69%, wind {{convert|8|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Ben Dreith]]\n |TV=[[Monday Night Football|ABC]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Al Michaels]] (play-by-play), [[Frank Gifford]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198612010sfo.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Giants|HomeName=49ers|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=0:25\n| Team=49ers\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=30\n| Kicker=[[Ray Wersching|Wersching]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=9:26\n| Team=49ers\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Jerry Rice|Rice]]\n| QB=[[Joe Montana|Montana]]\n| yards=11\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Ray Wersching|Wersching]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=10\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=0:45\n| Team=49ers\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Jerry Rice|Rice]]\n| yards=1\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Ray Wersching|Wersching]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=12:19\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=17\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=7:37\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Stacy Robinson|Robinson]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=34\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=14\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=3:41\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Ottis Anderson|Anderson]]\n| yards=1\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=21\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=21|Home=17}}\n\n====Week 14: at Washington Redskins====\n{{See also|1986 Washington Redskins season}}\n\nThe Giants defeated the Redskins 24\u201314 in week 14 to move into sole possession of first place in the NFC East.<ref name=\"Lead\">Janofsky, Michael. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50711F63F5B0C7B8CDDAB0994DE484D81 Alone at the Top: Giants Knock Out Redskins, 24\u201314; All Goes Wrong for Washington], ''The New York Times'', December 8, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> The Redskins held Joe Morris, who had rushed for 181&nbsp;yards in the Giants week eight victory, to 62&nbsp;yards on 22 carries.<ref name=\"Lead\"/> However, Lawrence Taylor recorded three sacks and harassed Redskins' quarterback [[Jay Schroeder]] all game, as the Giants recorded four sacks and the Redskins only recorded one.<ref name=\"Lead\"/> Phil Simms threw touchdown passes to Mark Bavaro, [[Bobby Johnson]], and Phil McConkey in the victory.<ref>Anderson, Dave. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50717FC355B0C7B8CDDAB0994DE484D81 Sports of the Times; Another Day in Surgery], ''The New York Times'', December 8, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> Schroeder threw six interceptions in the game, matching [[Sammy Baugh]]'s franchise record,<ref name=\"Lead\"/> and the Redskins had 7 [[Turnover (football)|turnovers]] overall.<ref>[http://databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=7&mth=12&yr=1986&tm=WAS&lg=NFL Box Score Giants Vs Redskins 12/7/1986] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060526063102/http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=7&mth=12&yr=1986&tm=WAS&lg=NFL |date=May 26, 2006 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> After the game, Parcells gave the Redskins credit for their performance and told the reporters that he had a feeling that the two would meet again sometime in the playoffs.\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 14: New York Giants at Washington Redskins\n |date=December 7, 1986\n |time=1:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n |road='''Giants (12\u20132)'''\n |R1=0|R2=14|R3=10|R4=0|RT=24\n |home=Redskins (11\u20133)\n |H1=0|H2=7|H3=0|H4=7|HT=14\n |stadium=[[RFK Stadium]]\n |attendance=55,642\n |weather={{convert|38|F}}, relative humidity 69%, wind {{convert|8|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Red Cashion]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Pat Summerall]] (play-by-play), [[John Madden (American football)|John Madden]] (color commentator), [[Irv Cross]] (sideline reporter)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198612070was.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Giants|HomeName=Redskins|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=8:35\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Mark Bavaro|Bavaro]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=9\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=1:55\n| Team=Redskins\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Kelvin Bryant|Bryant]]\n| yards=4\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Max Zendejas|Zendejas]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=7\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=0:23\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Bobby Johnson (American football)|Johnson]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=7\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=14\n| Home=7\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=4:33\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=21\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=17\n| Home=7\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=3:11\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Phil McConkey|McConkey]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=16\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=24\n| Home=7\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=3:24\n| Team=Redskins\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Kelvin Bryant|Bryant]]\n| QB=[[Jay Schroeder|Schroeder]]\n| yards=22\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Max Zendejas|Zendejas]]\n| Visitor=24\n| Home=14\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=24|Home=14}}\n\n====Week 15: vs. St. Louis Cardinals====\n{{See also|1986 St. Louis Cardinals (NFL) season}}\n\nThe Giants defeated the St. Louis Cardinals 27\u20137 in their fifteenth game of the season in front of 75,261 fans at Giants Stadium.<ref name=\"Rolling\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F5071EF634590C768DDDAB0994DE484D81 Giants Keep Rolling Around], ''The New York Times'', December 15, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> Joe Morris ran for 179&nbsp;yards and three touchdowns, but had three fumbles.<ref name=\"Rolling\"/> Phil Simms struggled, but the offense was effective nonetheless;<ref name=\"Rolling\"/> of the Giants 313 total yards, 252 came on the ground, while only 62 came from the passing game.<ref name=\"Simms62\">[http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=14&mth=12&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL Box Score Cardinal Vs Giants 12/14/1986] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111122014853/http://databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=14&mth=12&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL |date=November 22, 2011 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 20, 2007.</ref> The Giants defense controlled the Cardinals throughout the game, particularly in the first half; the Cardinals' first four possessions ended in third-down sacks and fourth-down punts.<ref name=\"Rolling\"/> The Giants committed only two penalties for a total of ten yards,<ref name=\"Simms62\"/> and their defense set a franchise record with nine sacks, despite sending Lawrence Taylor into pass coverage for most of the game.<ref name=\"Rolling\"/>  With the victory the Giants clinched their first NFC East division crown.\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 15: St. Louis Cardinals at New York Giants\n |date=December 14, 1986\n |time=1:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n |road=Cardinals (3\u201311\u20131)\n |R1=0|R2=0|R3=0|R4=7|RT=7\n |home='''Giants (13\u20132)'''\n |H1=7|H2=10|H3=3|H4=7|HT=27\n |stadium=[[Giants Stadium]]\n |attendance=75,261\n |weather={{convert|26|F}}, relative humidity 46%, wind {{convert|14|mph|abbr=on}}, wind chill {{convert|14|F}}\n |referee=[[Bob McElwee]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Jack Buck]] (play-by-play), [[Joe Theismann]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198612140nyg.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Cardinals|HomeName=Giants|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=4:39\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=2\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=7\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=3:29\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=3\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=14\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=0:11\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=26\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=3:30\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=23\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=20\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=6:37\n| Team=Cardinals\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Roy Green|Green]]\n| QB=[[Stump Mitchell|Mitchell]]\n| yards=15\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Steve Schubert|Schubert]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=20\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=1:57\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=1\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=27\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=7|Home=27}}\n\n====Week 16: vs. Green Bay Packers====\n{{See also|1986 Green Bay Packers season}}\n\nThe Giants headed into their final regular season game against the [[Green Bay Packers]] as 11\u00bd-point favorites and needed a victory to secure homefield advantage throughout the playoffs.<ref name=\"Home\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50712FE38540C738EDDAB0994DE484D81 Giants Seek Edge for Playoffs], ''The New York Times'', December 20, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> Sparked by a blocked punt returned for a TD by Tom Flynn, who had recently been picked up from the Packers, the Giants defeated the Packers 55\u201324 in front of 71,351 fans at Giants Stadium to finish the regular season with a franchise record 14 victories.<ref name=\"Packers\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50716F8385C0C728EDDAB0994DE484D81 Giants Stay Home for Playoffs], ''The New York Times'', December 21, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> The win was the Giants' ninth consecutive, matching the team record set in 1962.<ref name=\"Packers\"/> The Giants also set a franchise record for points in the first quarter of a game with 21.<ref name=\"Packers\"/> Although the Packers cut the score to 24\u201317 at halftime, the Giants scored 31 second half points to put the game out of reach.\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 16: Green Bay Packers at New York Giants\n |date=December 20, 1986\n |time=12:30 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n |road=Packers (4\u201312)\n |R1=0|R2=17|R3=7|R4=0|RT=24\n |home='''Giants (14\u20132)'''\n |H1=21|H2=3|H3=14|H4=17|HT=55\n |stadium=[[Giants Stadium]]\n |attendance=71,351\n |weather={{convert|39|F}}, relative humidity 63%, wind {{convert|13|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Fred Silva]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Dick Stockton]] (play-by-play), [[Dan Dierdorf]] (color commentator), [[John Dockery]] (sideline reporter)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198612200nyg.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Packers|HomeName=Giants|state=collapse}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=8:25\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Mark Bavaro|Bavaro]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=24\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=7\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=7:23\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=Other\n| Other=[[Tom Flynn (American football)|Flynn]] returned blocked punt 36 yards for a touchdown, [[Raul Allegre|Allegre]] kick good\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=14\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=0:38\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=3\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=21\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=8:08\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=46\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=24\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=4:11\n| Team=Packers\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Eddie Lee Ivery|Ivery]]\n| QB=[[Randy Wright|Wright]]\n| yards=13\n| kickresult=