 and 14 at the end, he was trying to make a play. I think I would have thrown there, too. The other interception was his mistake. I don't think he's in a slump.\"<ref name=\"int\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50717F63D5B0C728EDDA90994DE484D81 Giants are seeking to Mend Offense], ''The New York Times'', October 21, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants}}; {{NFLSecondaryStyle|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 7: New York Giants at Seattle Seahawks\n |date=October 19, 1986\n |time=4:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]\n |road=Giants (5\u20132)\n |R1=0|R2=9|R3=0|R4=3|RT=12\n |home='''Seahawks (5\u20132)'''\n |H1=7|H2=0|H3=3|H4=7|HT=17\n |stadium=[[Kingdome]]\n |attendance=62,282\n |weather=indoors (dome)\n |referee=[[Gene Barth]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Pat Summerall]] (play-by-play), [[John Madden (American football)|John Madden]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198610190sea.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Giants|HomeName=Seahawks|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=7:51\n| Team=Seahawks\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Gordon Hudson|Hudson]]\n| QB=[[Dave Krieg|Krieg]]\n| yards=16\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Norm Johnson|Johnson]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=7\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=11:50\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Solomon Miller|Miller]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=32\n| kickresult=no good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=6\n| Home=7\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=0:41\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=23\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=9\n| Home=7\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=7:03\n| Team=Seahawks\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=25\n| Kicker=[[Norm Johnson|Johnson]]\n| Visitor=9\n| Home=10\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=10:00\n| Team=Seahawks\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Curt Warner|Warner]]\n| yards=1\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Norm Johnson|Johnson]]\n| Visitor=9\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=4:42\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=31\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=12\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=12|Home=17}}\n\n====Week 8: vs. Washington Redskins====\n{{See also|1986 Washington Redskins season}}\n\nOn the same night the [[New York Mets]] would come from behind to defeat the [[Boston Red Sox]] in Game 7 of the [[1986 World Series]], the Giants defeated the Redskins 27\u201320 in week eight to improve to 6\u20132 and move into a tie with the Redskins for the division lead.<ref name=\"Redskins\">Listky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50716F63C590C7B8EDDA90994DE484D81 Giants defeat Redskins and Tie for Lead], ''The New York Times'', October 28, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> With the teams tied 20\u201320, Joe Morris scored the game-winning touchdown on a 13-yard run with 98 seconds remaining.<ref name=\"Redskins\"/> The Giants offense featured a two tight end formation throughout much of the game which allowed them to run the ball more effectively.<ref name=\"twotight\">Janofsky, Michael. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F5071FF73C590C7B8EDDA90994DE484D81 2 Tight-End Setup Helps Giants Win], ''The New York Times'', October 28, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> The Giants used [[Mark Bavaro]] and Zeke Mowatt throughout much of the game, sometimes even lining them up on the same side.<ref name=\"twotight\"/> Morris finished the game with 181&nbsp;yards.<ref name=\"Lead\"/> Redskins quarterback [[Jay Schroeder]] threw for 420&nbsp;yards in the loss.<ref>Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F5071EF639540C7A8CDDAB0994DE484D81 Giants Were Winners in Battle of Wits], ''The New York Times'', December 9, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryColor|New York Giants}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 8: Washington Redskins at New York Giants\n |date=October 27, 1986\n |time=9:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n |road=Redskins (6\u20132)\n |R1=0|R2=3|R3=14|R4=3|RT=20\n |home='''Giants (6\u20132)'''\n |H1=3|H2=10|H3=7|H4=7|HT=27\n |stadium=[[Giants Stadium]]\n |attendance=75,923\n |weather={{convert|52|F}}, relative humidity 97%, wind {{convert|14|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Jerry Seeman]]\n |TV=[[Monday Night Football|ABC]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Al Michaels]] (play-by-play), [[Frank Gifford]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198610270nyg.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Redskins|HomeName=Giants|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=10:00\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=37\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=12:28\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=11\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=10\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=3:21\n| Team=Redskins\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=23\n| Kicker=[[Max Zendejas|Zendejas]]\n| Visitor=3\n| Home=10\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=0:00\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=44\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=3\n| Home=13\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=9:04\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Bobby Johnson (American football)|Johnson]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=25\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=3\n| Home=20\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=6:57\n| Team=Redskins\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[George Rogers (American football)|Rogers]]\n| yards=1\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Max Zendejas|Zendejas]]\n| Visitor=10\n| Home=20\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=4:12\n| Team=Redskins\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Gary Clark|Clark]]\n| QB=[[Jay Schroeder|Schroeder]]\n| yards=42\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Max Zendejas|Zendejas]]\n| Visitor=17\n| Home=20\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=4:06\n| Team=Redskins\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=29\n| Kicker=[[Max Zendejas|Zendejas]]\n| Visitor=20\n| Home=20\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=1:38\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=13\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=20\n| Home=27\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=20|Home=27}}\n\n====Week 9: vs. Dallas Cowboys====\n{{See also|1986 Dallas Cowboys season}}\n\nThe Giants played the Cowboys at Giants Stadium in week nine.<ref name=\"Boys\">Litsky, Frank. The Beat Gets Stronger for Jets (8\u20131) and Giants (7\u20132), ''The New York Times'', November 3, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> Defensive end [[George Martin (American football)|George Martin]] recorded a late sack, termed by head coach Bill Parcells as the biggest play of the game, to help the Giants to a 17\u201314 victory.<ref name=\"Boys\"/> The Giants held running backs Tony Dorsett to 45&nbsp;yards in 10 carries and Herschel Walker to 34&nbsp;yards in 10 carries.<ref name=\"Boys\"/> The Cowboys outgained the Giants 408 to 245 in total yardage, and had 25 first downs compared with the Giants' 14.<ref>[http://databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=2&mth=11&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL Box Score Cowboys Vs Giants 11/2/1986] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060526062957/http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=2&mth=11&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL |date=May 26, 2006 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> Phil Simms struggled and completed only 6 of 18 passes for 67&nbsp;yards,<ref name=\"Vikings\"/> but Joe Morris rushed 29 times for 181&nbsp;yards and two touchdowns as the Giants improved to 7\u20132.<ref name=\"Boys\"/>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryColor|New York Giants}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 9: Dallas Cowboys at New York Giants\n |date=November 2, 1986\n |time=1:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n |road=Cowboys (6\u20133)\n |R1=0|R2=7|R3=0|R4=7|RT=14\n |home='''Giants (7\u20132)'''\n |H1=3|H2=7|H3=0|H4=7|HT=17\n |stadium=[[Giants Stadium]]\n |attendance=74,871\n |weather={{convert|59|F}}, relative humidity 83%, wind {{convert|14|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Dick Hantak]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Pat Summerall]] (play-by-play), [[John Madden (American football)|John Madden]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198611020nyg.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Cowboys|HomeName=Giants|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=2:29\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=25\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=11:00\n| Team=Cowboys\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Mike Renfro|Renfro]]\n| QB=[[Steve Pelluer|Pelluer]]\n| yards=11\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Rafael Septien|Septien]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=6:24\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=8\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=10\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=12:24\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=6\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=7:29\n| Team=Cowboys\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Tony Dorsett|Dorsett]]\n| yards=23\n| kickresult=ggood\n| Kicker=[[Rafael Septien|Septien]]\n| Visitor=14\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=14|Home=17}}\n\n====Week 10: at Philadelphia Eagles====\n{{See also|1986 Philadelphia Eagles season}}\n\nIn week 10, the Giants then travelled to Philadelphia to play the Eagles.<ref name=\"Ground\">Litsky, Frank [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50713FC3E550C728DDDA80994DE484D81 Jets Stay in Air; Giants Grounded; Robinson Gets Better], November 11, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> In a physical game marked by several scuffles,<ref name=\"Clamp\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50712F73D5A0C738DDDA80994DE484D81 Giants Put a Clamp on Eagles], ''The New York Times'', November 10, 1986, accessed May 18, 2007.</ref> the Giants passing game struggled as several receivers played with injuries, and quarterback Phil Simms completed only one pass to a wide receiver; a 17-yarder to [[Solomon Miller]].<ref name=\"Ground\"/> Coach Bill Parcells placed the blame for the passing game's performance on dropped passes by the receivers. \"You can't throw the ball much better than Phil did yesterday\", commented Parcells. \"But he didn't have the numbers to show for it.\"<ref name=\"Ground\"/> The Eagles rushed for 153&nbsp;yards and outgained the Giants 265 to 237 in total yards.<ref>[http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=9&mth=11&yr=1986&tm=PHI&lg=NFL Box Score Giants Vs Eagles 11/9/1986] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060920130714/http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=9&mth=11&yr=1986&tm=PHI&lg=NFL |date=September 20, 2006 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 20, 2007.</ref> The Giants won 17\u201314 nonetheless despite Simms completing only 14 of 36 passes overall. The Giants rode their running attack as Joe Morris passed the 100&nbsp;yard mark for the fourth consecutive game; Morris totalled 116, 181, 181 and 111&nbsp;yards in that period.<ref name=\"Ground\"/> Lawrence Taylor recorded three sacks of the Giants defense seven sacks in the victory.<ref name=\"Clamp\"/>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryColor|New York Giants}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 10: New York Giants at Philadelphia Eagles\n |date=November 9, 1986\n |time=4:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n |road='''Giants (8\u20132)'''\n |R1=0|R2=10|R3=7|R4=0|RT=17\n |home=Eagles (3\u20137)\n |H1=0|H2=0|H3=0|H4=14|HT=14\n |stadium=[[Veterans Stadium]]\n |attendance=60,601\n |weather={{convert|64|F}}, realative humidity 93%, wind {{convert|12|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Fred Wyant]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Pat Summerall]] (play-by-play), [[John Madden (American football)|John Madden]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198611090phi.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Giants|HomeName=Eagles|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=10:20\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=18\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=0:01\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=25\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=10\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=10:04\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=3\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=17\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=8:49\n| Team=Eagles\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Mike Quick|Quick]]\n| QB=[[Randall Cunningham|Cunningham]]\n| yards=75\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Paul McFadden|McFadden]]\n| Visitor=17\n| Home=7\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=0:45\n| Team=Eagles\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Randall Cunningham|Cunningham]]\n| yards=4\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Paul McFadden|McFadden]]\n| Visitor=17\n| Home=14\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=17|Home=14}}\n\n====Week 11: at Minnesota Vikings====\n{{See also|1986 Minnesota Vikings season}}\n\nTrailing the [[Minnesota Vikings]] 20\u201319 with 72 seconds left in the fourth quarter at the [[Hubert H. Humphrey Metrodome|Metrodome]] in week 11, Phil Simms completed a desperate 22-yard pass on fourth and 17 to Bobby Johnson for a first down.<ref name=\"Po29\">Pooley. pg. 29</ref><ref name=\"Litsky\"/> The completion led to [[Raul Allegre]]'s fifth field goal and an important Giants victory 22\u201320.<ref name=\"Vikings\"/> In the Giants' three previous games, Simms had completed only six passes to wide receivers. In the Giants' victory he completed eight to wide receivers, four to tight end Mark Bavaro and 13 to his running backs\u2014four to [[Ottis Anderson]] in the final two drives, three to [[Maurice Carthon]], three to Joe Morris and three to [[Tony Galbreath]].<ref name=\"Vikings\">[[Dave Anderson (sportswriter)|Anderson, Dave]]. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50716F6345E0C748DDDA80994DE484D81 Sports Of The Times; Phil Simms's Biggest Pass], ''The New York Times'', November 17, 1986. accessed March 20, 2007.</ref> Simms commented years later, \"[i]t's my favorite game in my career, because it's everything I always wanted to be as a player. I wanted to be tough, making big throws, immune to pressure, not worried about outcomes. It was truly like standing on the tee box in golf and there's trees on each side and water and you just go 'Man, I'm gonna rip it down the middle.' And no other thought crosses your mind.\"<ref>Schwartz. pg. 161</ref> The game has frequently been credited as a signature game of their season, and the Giants players celebrated the victory in the tunnel leading to their locker room and in the locker room itself in a raucous manner that was highly atypical for the team. \"They high-fived themselves silly\", recalled [[Peter King (sportswriter)|Peter King]]. \"They were screaming and hooting and raising hell\u2014happier than they had been all year.\"<ref name=\"Po29\"/>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryColor|New York Giants}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 11: New York Giants at Minnesota Vikings\n |date=November 16, 1986\n |time=1:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n |road='''Giants (9\u20132)'''\n |R1=3|R2=6|R3=3|R4=10|RT=22\n |home=Vikings (6\u20135)\n |H1=3|H2=3|H3=7|H4=7|HT=20\n |stadium=[[Hubert H. Humphrey Metrodome]]\n |attendance=62,003\n |